# Release Notes – ENDOS Foundation Release V1.1

## Release Name

ENDOS Foundation Release V1.1

## Release Objective

Transform the initial GitHub Pages deployment into a professional project foundation with stronger documentation, improved landing page and a clearer sprint roadmap.

## Included

- Modernized `index.html`
- New stylesheet in `assets/css/style.css`
- JavaScript placeholder in `assets/js/app.js`
- Expanded `README.md`
- New `CHANGELOG.md`
- New `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- New `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`
- New `docs/ROADMAP.md`
- New `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- New `docs/VISION.md`
- New `docs/FAQ.md`
- New repository, research, patent, pilot and release folders

## Strategic Meaning

This release marks the transition from a simple web presence to a structured platform foundation. It prepares ENDOS for:

- Sprint-based development
- Professional versioning
- Partner and pilot communication
- Architecture consolidation
- Evidence and validation work

